{% raw %}
{% endraw %}

  • [cFOS_Wue]: Trained on 36 image-mask pairs of cFOS labels in the dorsal hippocampus (including 12 images of each sub-region: dentate gyrus, CA3 and CA1). Masks for training were prepared by five independent experts. Images were acquired using laser-scanning confocal microscopy with a resolution of 1.6 pixel per µm.

  • [Parv]: Trained on 36 image-mask pairs of Parvalbumin-labels in the dorsal hippocampus (including 12 images of each sub-region: dentate gyrus, CA3 and CA1). Masks for training were prepared by five independent experts. Images were acquired using laser-scanning confocal microscopy with a resolution of 1.6 pixel per µm.

  • [cFOS_Inns1]: with five image-mask pairs of cFOS labels in the amygdala. Masks for fine-tuning were prepared by one expert. Images acquired using epifluorescence microscopy with a resolution of 1 pixel per µm.

  • [cFOS_Inns2]: with five image-mask pairs of cFOS labels in the infralimbic cortex. Masks for fine-tuning were prepared by one expert. Images acquired using epifluorescence microscopy with a resolution of 2 pixel per µm.

  • [cFOS_Mue]: with five image-mask pairs of cFOS labels in the paraventricular nucleus of the thalamus. Masks for fine-tuning were prepared by one expert. Images acquired using laser-scanning confocal microscopy with a resolution of 0.8 pixel per µm.
